I finally attained the RBF on July 16th.<br>
<br>
On the first day, I spent bout 4 hours camping the mob, everything was green to me with the occasional Froglock Ton Warrior being blue.  Nothing problematic.  However, I never attained the RBF.<br>
<br>
On the second day, I spent about 3 hours doing the camp.  This time things were bad as I was having a really hard time killing the PH.  He was up for so long that a roaming Neophyte had SOWed him.  Everytime I got the PH weak, he'd run and I would be unable to keep up.  Always caused a massive train and had to zone.  Eventually with the help of a nice Mage who rooted it for me, I was able to get things going.  The next 2 hours or so I never got the RBF.  Did manage to get one Collar though.<br>
<br>
Third day, camp is empty.  Camp for about 4 hours, no luck.  A young Mage, level 21, wanted a group, so I grouped him.  He summoned me food/drinks/daggers/bandaids and rooted, and I in turn gave him free nice XP.  I leveled him too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Final day in this camp, I spend 6 hours.  I'm ticked, frustrated, venting to all my friends (thanks Bunyun) about how I'm the unluckiest SOB in the world.  Of course, some of my friends (thanks Pugs) rub it in how the Squire with RBF was up as soon as they got to UGuk.  Don't wanna hear that!  To make matters worse, when I arrive, the PH is once again SOWed.  After training everytime, a nice Necro named Parrel zones, and I ask him for a snare.  He does.  Thanks!  Things are going smoothly, but Parrel, upon leaving tells me that someone in UGuk is a Neutral Druid.  I was too bent on the camp to care much.  And then I got rooted and owned <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    This is the reason I want MR in the first place =P  So now I am hell-bent on getting revenge as well as keeping my camp!  I zone in, warn people, then group with a Shaman to seek out the bastard.  He heads to the AC since that's what he is likely camping at this early hour in the morning when UGuk has about 5 people in it.  I head to the Squire camp, thinking he'd be waiting for me to CR.  I successfully get my body and then I see him (I had See Invis from Shammy now), so I keep a low profile.  He finally catches a glimpse of me and high tails it.  I follow through UGuk.  He never loses me.  At this point we are in the room near Squire with the &quot;barrel&quot; texture on the wall.  He starts fighting me.  I resist his ensnare (he was even con to me) and I'm on him.  I'm taking down his HP, all the while he isn't moving, just casting Combust like a maniac.  I'm circle strafing and manage to land backstabs while he casts.  Ultimately though, with no Fire Resist, and no interruptions on his casting, he takes me out.  I am deleveled to 27 8(  Of course now I am MAD.  A friend asks me how I lost my level and I explain, so he heads to UGuk to help me.  We go in, get our corpse.  Ultimately, the Druid gets scared and gates out.  Back to my camp.  Another hour or so passes and I'm about to call it quits for the day.  With 5 minutes to go on the pop, I am receive a tell to join a Sol A group.  I say OK, but then apologize and decide to stick around for ONE more pop.  Next pop: PH.  Now I am kicking myself for not taking that group.  I kill this pop, then go afk before I break my computer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    15 minutes later I come and THE SQUIRE IS POPPED WITH THE RBF!  Of course like a giddy kid I lose my calm and rush into the fight head first.  Bad mistake, the Squire is popped, and I've just caused an idiotic train of 3 froggies.  I would surely have to zone this and possibly lose my precious RBF 8(  I decide to try desperately to kill the Squire, loot and zone asap.  So that's what I do.  As I'm mash the attack button I think to myself &quot;hmm, is the RBF magic?.&quot;  Lucky for me I didn't care, I mashed the DISARM button anyway.  To my shock I DISARMED THE RBF off the Squire!!!  Here I am getting whacked by 3 froggies, thinking that I'll die/zone and the RBF be taken by someone else, and the best thing I could ever imagine happens!  I quickly grab the damn bag, stuff it away, and zone the hell outta UGuk.  <br>
<br>
And of course, the first thing I do in Innothule is get rid of the ranged attack button <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
And that my friends, is my long but crazy tale of the RBF camp on SZ.  Hope you enjoyed!<br>
